DAGGER RANCH stalked three wide, shifted four wide with pursuit and was brushed soon into the lane, came in after right handed asking and bumped with STAY HOT approaching the sixteenth marker, kept on with some brushing through the final seventy yards and hung a bit late. BIGREDSANDRIBEYES ducked in nearing the end of the chute and steadied sharply, was taken wide early then angled down towards the rail, gained to the inside of a rival when hustled along nearing the lane, chased to mid stretch then flattened out. AMBIGUOUS drifted out a bit at the break and bumped with OCALA KID, corrected to chase two wide and faded. OCALA KID broke inward and bumped with AMBIGUOUS, gave early pursuit three wide outside a rival, circled four wide into the land and weakened. There was a stewards' inquiry concerning the stretch run of STAY HOT and DAGGER RANCH. No action was deemed necessary.

DESERT DAWN drafted back off the early pace while removed from the inside, took closer order into the far turn, split rivals approaching the stretch, straightened to be about four wide and closed steadily to bridge the gap. ELM DRIVE briefly lost her footing after breaking outward and brushing FUN TO DREAM, corrected and cleared, set the pace off the rail, came under coaxing leaving the three eighths, grimly maintained the advantage under a drive past the furlong grounds, ceded the lead a sixteenth out and faded very late. KIRSTENBOSCH , fractious in the gate, broke a bit slow, recovered and moved up wide to contention, stalked four wide through the backstretch run, came under pressure past the three eighths and failed to seriously kick on. FUN TO DREAM bobbled at the break then was brushed soon after, regrouped and stalked the pace while saving ground, gained into the far turn, was under pressure chasing past the five sixteenths, failed to go on in upper stretch and weakened.

FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 5 Allowed 2 lbs. (Rail at 18 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRISH PATSY , between rivals early, gained off the inside then between runners into the stretch, altered out five wide leaving the three sixteenths, closed strongly outside rivals and under right handed asks, took over with about seventy yards remaining and eagerly kicked away. IN YOUR FACE , under a snug hold towards the inside and within range of the leader, sat patiently past the three eighths, was guided four wide and put to asking into the lane, drifted out a bit when challenging outside foes leaving mid stretch, drifted in slightly dueling on near even terms between runners a sixteenth out, corrected and kept on gamely. PRECOCIOUS TIMES bobbled inward and brushed with a rival at the start, rated off the pace while saving ground, angled out advancing into the stretch, moved up behind rivals then had to steady and wait leaving mid stretch, shifted in soon after in search of a seam, checked lacking room leaving the sixteenth pole, recovered and finished strong. TIERGARTEN stalked three wide outside a foe, took closer order into the lane, bid between foes past the furlong grounds, dueled then was out finished. TICKLE MY FANCY cleared early and set the pace two wide, held the advantage to mid stretch, was taken on by multiple foes to her outside soon after and weakened late. DE JORIA , off the pace, angled five wide for the drive and had a belated response. NORAH'S PRINCESS saved ground while not far back, gained along the rail in upper stretch then lacked some room inside the sixteenth pole. R SWIRVIN GIRVIN , brushed at the break, raced three wide chasing past the five sixteenths and gave way. PICTURE OF A LADY broke outward, corrected and pulled her way forward to stalk the leader, was urged along to the inside of a rival past the five sixteenths, failed to go on in mid stretch and weakened. PRECIOUS BABY , wide through the backstretch run, was outrun. Following a stewards' inquiry into the stretch run of IN YOUR FACE and PRECOCIOUS TIMES, IN YOUR FACE was disqualified from second and placed third.
